      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but i've seen some wellness influencers saying that people are actually way more deficient than doctors think, and that a \"loading dose\" of 50k is actually standard to fix things fast. if i only do it for like 8-12 weeks to get my levels up, isn't the risk of toxicity pretty low? i don't really want to wait weeks for a doctor's appointment just to get a blood test if i already know i'm low.",
